title: "Robert Frost - Silence"
date: 2024-12-29 12:00:00 -0000
author: Robert Frost
quote: "The woods are warm and fragrant,"
subject: American Nature Poets (19th century)
permalink: /American Nature Poets (19th century)/Robert Frost/Robert Frost - Silence
---

The woods are warm and fragrant,
Spilled with sunshine and dew,
Here I’ll wander on and take,
The beauty surrounding you.

I’ll lose myself in this quiet place,
Till all longing is drowned in delight;
And there let me feel once again,
The wonder of nature ignite the night.

- Robert Frost
